Type

* code 730 is used to indicate previous transactions of the e-TTN type
* code 730 is also used when creating acts to indicate the e-TTN for which the act is created
* code 916 is used when forming acts to indicate the previous transaction of the current act
* code 723 when specifying a document confirming the provision of special security services
* code 290 when specifying the transfer of the right to submit a claim
* code 119 in operations with the act of loading at an intermediate warehouse, to indicate the previous act of unloading at the same warehouse
